value.value: 呼吸器系の表現型

the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the mammalian system responsible for the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide with the environment that are manifested through development and lifespan
生殖系の表現型
the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the mammalian organs associated with producing offspring that are manifested through development and lifespan
骨格の表現型

the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the bone, cartilage, teeth, tendons, ligaments and other associated tissues of the bony framework ot the body of a mammalian organism that are manifested through development and lifespan
視覚／眼の表現型
the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the mammalian spheroid organ and optic nerve that serve to detect light that are manifested through development and lifespan
味覚／嗅覚の表現型
the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the organs involved in and perception of taste and smell in a mammalian organism that are manifested through development and lifespan
造血系の表現型

the observable morphological and physiological characteristics of the mammalian blood cells or the organs associated with the development and formation of blood cells that are manifested through development and lifespan
真菌感染に対する感受性低下
reduced likelihood that an organism will develop ill effects from infection by a yeast or mold, or from components of, or toxins produced by, these organisms
真菌感染に対する感受性上昇
greater likelihood that an organism will develop ill effects from infection by a yeast or mold, or from components of, or toxins produced by, these organisms
ビタミン値の異常
any anomaly in the concentration of any of the organic substances found in food that are necessary in trace amounts for normal metabolic function
脂溶性ビタミンの濃度異常

any anomaly in the concentration of any of the organic substances found in food that are necessary in trace amounts for normal metabolic function and which require the presence of lipids for assimilation in the body
活動電位異常
change in the electric response of a nerve or other excitable tissue to its stimulation
神経伝導の異常
anomaly in the act of transmitting electricity along a single nerve
軸索形態異常
any structural anomaly of the single process of a nerve cell that normally conducts impulses away from the cell body
軸索変性
retrogressive pathologic change in the single process of a nerve cell
心臓サイズの異常
change from normal in the physical magnitude of the cardiac muscle or any of its component structures
痛覚過敏

increased sensitivity to painful stimuli; can be due to inflammatory response or due to damage to soft tissue containing nociceptors or injury to a peripheral nerve; it can be primary (at the site of the injury) or secondary (in the surrounding undamaged area)
低色素沈着
dilution of pigment in any or all tissues or a part of a tissue
濃い毛色
amount and distribution of yellow pigment (phaeomelanin) relative to black or brown pigment (eumelanin) is decreased when compared to wild-type agouti
受精の異常
anomaly in the process beginning with penetration of the secondary oocyte by the spermatozoon and completed by fusion of the male and female pronuclei
受精の遅延
a lag in the normal time of onset of the process beginning with penetration of the secondary oocyte by the spermatozoon and completed by fusion of the male and female pronuclei
血管性狭窄症
abnormal narrowing or constriction of the lumen of one or more blood vessels
血管性再狭窄
recurrence of a narrowing or constriction of a blood vessel following surgical or mechanical removal or reduction of a previous narrowing
肝臓外の胆汁鬱帯
impairment of bile flow in the large bile ducts by mechanical obstruction or stricture due to benign or malignant process
肝臓内の胆汁鬱帯
impairment of bile flow due to injury to the hepatocytes, bile canaliculi, or the intrahepatic bile ducts
蛋白質血中濃度異常
anomaly in the amount in the blood of any of the macromolecules consisting of long chains of amino acids in peptide linkage
ホルモン血中濃度異常

any anomaly in the blood concentration of any of the chemical substances that have specific regulatory effects on the activity of a certain organ or organs; originally applied to substances secreted by various endocrine glands and transported in the bloodstream to the target organs, it is sometimes extended to include substances that are not produced by the endocrine glands but that have similar effects
血清アルブミン血中濃度低下
blood serum albumin concentration below the normal range
弛緩性皮膚
condition in which the skin hangs in folds
骨硬化症
abnormal hardening or eburnation (change in exposed subchondral bone in degenerative joint disease in which bone is converted into a dense substance with a smooth surface) of bone
体細胞性神経系の生理異常

any functional anomaly of the part of the peripheral nervous system that is responsible for conveying voluntary motor and external sensory information, including all nerves controlling the skeletal muscular system and external sensory receptors (including balance, smell, sight, taste, touch and hearing sensory inputs)
ギクシャクした動作
continuous, abrupt, faltering motions of the whole body or a portion of the body
マクロファージ細胞数の増加
greater than the normal numbers of macrophages
頻呼吸症
rapid breathing
腓骨の欠如
absence of the lateral and shorter of the two bones of the lower leg
卵母細胞数の減少
reduced numbers of germ cells in the female
pro-B 細胞の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the progenitor cells of the B cell lineage, with some lineage specific activity such as early stages of recombination of B cell receptor genes, but are not yet fully committed to the B cell lineage until the expression of PAX5 occurs
初期pro-B 細胞の欠如
absence of cells in the B lymphocyte lineage that undergo D-J rearrangement of the immunoglobulin heavy chain
後期pro-Bの欠如
absence of the cells in the B lymphocyte lineage that undergo V-DJ rearrangement of the immunoglobulin heavy chain
腹腔内出血
blood in the peritoneal cavity
グリコーゲン値異常
any anomaly in the concentration of this readily converted carbohydrate reserve, found in most tissues of the body, especially liver and muscle
グリコーゲンの恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of glycogen, a readily converted carbohydrate reserve found in most tissues of the body, especially liver and muscle
グリコーゲン値低下
less than the normal concentration of a readily converted carbohydrate reserve, found in most tissues of the body, especially liver and muscle
グリコーゲン値上昇
greater than the normal concentration of this readily converted carbohydrate reserve, found in most tissues of the body, especially liver and muscle
尿中カルシウム濃度上昇
abnormally large amounts of calcium in the urine
エタノールの代謝異常
altered ability to metabolize the clear, colorless liquid that has formula C2H6O
レチノール代謝異常
altered ability to metabolize retinol, which plays an essential role in metabolic functioning of the retina, and growth of and differentiation
神経伝達物質の分泌異常

anomaly in the production or release of endogenous signaling molecules into a synaptic cleft; neurotransmitters are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell
シナプスのエピネフリン放出異常

aberrant secretion across synapses of the active sympathomimetic hormone that stimulates both the alpha- and beta- adrenergic systems, causes systemic vasoconstriction and gastrointestinal relaxation, stimulates the heart, and dilates bronchi and cerebral vessels
シナプスのノルエピネフリン放出異常

aberrant secretion across synapses of this widespread central and autonomic neurotransmitter, the principal transmitter of most postganglionic sympathetic fibers and of the diffuse projection system in the brain arising from the locus ceruleus
エネルギーバランスの異常
any anomaly in the process involved in the balance between food intake (energy input) and energy expenditure
